3.20	Chloroma	Myeloid sarcoma	A myeloid sarcoma , is a solid tumor composed of immature white blood cells called myeloblasts. A chloroma is an extramedullary manifestation of acute myeloid leukemia; in other words, it is a solid collection of leukemic cells occurring outside of the bone marrow.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/18/Chloroma_-_very_high_mag.jpg/230px-Chloroma_-_very_high_mag.jpg
